# üìÑ Privacy Policy for Grandma's Guardian

**Effective Date:** 7/28/2025

## Overview

**Grandma's Guardian** is a browser extension designed to protect users from scams, phishing attempts, and malicious downloads by enforcing domain and MIME-type allowlisting and filtering scam-related text content. This extension operates entirely on the user's device and does **not** collect, transmit, or store any personal or browsing data.

## Data Collection

Grandma's Guardian **does not collect any user data**. Specifically:

- ‚ùå No personally identifiable information (PII) is collected  
- ‚ùå No browsing history, URLs, or page content is transmitted to external servers  
- ‚ùå No analytics, tracking, or telemetry mechanisms are used  
- ‚ùå No user input, settings, or allowlists are synced or shared externally  

All filtering and protection features are performed locally within the browser.

## Permissions

The extension requests certain permissions (e.g., access to all URLs, downloads, storage) solely to enable its core functionality:

- ‚úÖ Blocking access to unsafe domains  
- ‚úÖ Preventing downloads of disallowed file types  
- ‚úÖ Hiding scam-related text on webpages  
- ‚úÖ Storing user-defined allowlists and preferences locally  

These permissions are **not used to collect or transmit data**.

## Third Parties

Grandma's Guardian does **not share data with any third parties**, nor does it integrate with any external services, APIs, or advertising networks.

## User Control

All settings and allowlists are fully controlled by the user and stored locally. Users may modify or delete these settings at any time via the extension‚Äôs popup interface.

## Policy Updates

This privacy policy may be updated to reflect changes in functionality or compliance requirements. However, any future version will continue to uphold the principle of **no data collection or transmission**.

